The Indiana University Computer Science Department used to be housed in Lindley Hall. In the basement was a cluster of machines called &ldquo;The Burrow&rdquo;. There were SparcStations, if memory serves with Sun Type 5 keyboards. In any case, they taught me that the good Lord intended Control to be to the immediate left of A.
